# Claude Configuration for PrepSense Project

## Commit Message Guidelines

**IMPORTANT**: Do NOT include any references to Claude, AI, or automated generation in commit messages.

Specifically, avoid:
- Any mention of "Claude" or "claude"
- "ðŸ¤– Generated with [Claude Code]" or similar
- "Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>"
- Any references to AI assistance or automated generation

## Commit Message Format

Use conventional commit format:
```
<type>: <description>

<body>

<footer>
```

Types:
- feat: new feature
- fix: bug fix
- docs: documentation changes
- style: formatting changes
- refactor: code restructuring
- perf: performance improvements
- test: adding tests
- chore: maintenance tasks

## Git Configuration

This project has the following git configurations:
1. Global commit template: ~/.gitmessage
2. Git hook: .git/hooks/prepare-commit-msg (removes Claude references automatically)
3. User config: PrepSense Team <team@prepsense.com>

## Note for AI Assistants

When creating commits in this repository:
1. Use descriptive, professional commit messages
2. Focus on what changed and why
3. Do NOT include any AI/Claude attribution
4. Follow the conventional commit format above